</head><body><table width=90% align=center><tr><td class=textbody><center><h1>Lvl 34-43: Eastern Wastes</h1><br>by Shafli Tritium</center><br><table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="border-collapse: collapse" bordercolor="#111111" width="531" id="AutoNumber1">
  <tr>
    <td width="531">
    <p align="left"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: Verdana"><font color="#FFFFFF"><b>34-43, 
    Eastern Wastes</b></color><br>
    Minimum Level: 34<br>
    Maximum Level: 43<br>
    Zone Name: Eastern Wastes<br>
    Camp Area/LOC: The shore north of the bridge<br>
    Mob List (HP): Walruses, Uthork Hunters, Uthork Warriors <br>
    Availability (1->10): 5 <br>
    Loot Ranking (1->10): 6 <br>
    Diff.Ranking (1->10): 2 <br>
    Faction Affected: Othmir increased, Uthorks/Bulthars decreased<br>
    <br>
    Other Notes/Tips/Warnings: Avoid the rhinos, they run very fast, and are 
    quite resistant to spells. Begin with the walruses, and as they become light 
    blue, move up to Uthork Hunters and then Uthork Warriors. If you can only 
    find two (2) dark blue mobs, you might as well mix in a couple light blue or 
    greens to keep the spawns cycling and you'll be using the mana anyway, so 
    it's extra kills for free. Have something to make you run fast, and use 
    Bonds of Force (level 29) to snare and the researched Circle of Force (level 
    34) to nuke.</span></p>
    <ul>
      <li>
      <p align="left"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: Verdana">
      Great place to learn how to quad, plenty of room, easy to avoid adds.</span></li>
      <li>
      <p align="left"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: Verdana">
      Sometimes hard to find four (4) mobs due to other quadders.</span></li>
      <li>
      <p align="left"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: Verdana">
      Tusks can be traded in Cobalt Scar for gems, occasional research drops.<br>
      [if !supportLineBreakNewLine]<br>
 [endif]</span></li>
    </ul>
